   <teiHeader>
      <fileDesc>
         <titleStmt>
            <title type="short">Encoding Project</title>
            <title>An encoding of samples from a corpus of three different litterary works, for the last assignment for M2 TNAH's XML-TEI class </title>
            <respStmt>
               <resp>encoded by</resp>
               <name>Anaëlle Martinez</name>
            </respStmt>
         </titleStmt>
         <publicationStmt>
            <p>This ODD file has been generated from the Kafka-Milena correspondence project first. 
               This schema has been customized for encoding a literary corpus consisting of three diverse texts: 
                  Kafka's letters to Milena (to analyze emotional rhetoric), Anouilh's Antigone (to analyse speech acts 
                  and power dynamics), and Barjavel's La Faim du Tigre (to analyse philosophical argumentation). 
                  The schema constrains analytical markup to ensure consistency across the corpus while accommodating 
                  rhetorical features of each text type (personal correspondence, dramatic dialogue, and 
                  philosophical essay) and their analysis.</p>
            <p> 
               Three custom rules are implemented:
               (1) Closed value list for seg/@ana constraining analytical categories 
               (2) Structured content model requiring dateline to contain placeName followed by date(s)
               (3) Schematron constraint ensuring persName/@ref points to existing person/@xml:id declarations
            </p>
         </publicationStmt>
         <sourceDesc>
            <p>Derived from TEI-ALL and customized for a corpus of 3 literary works.</p>
         </sourceDesc>
      </fileDesc>
   </teiHeader>
